\n\\u2020 suwei@sicnu.edu.cn\\n\\u2021 rwang89@nju.edu.cn\\ning physics that drive the interplay between the Kondo\\nscreening and the QD-MZM coupling have been de-\\nbated for a long time [31\\u201335].\\nOn one hand, it has\\nbeen shown that at very low temperature, the system\\nis subjected to the A \\u2297N boundary condition (BC)\\ndue to the QD-MZM coupling [32]. Here A \\u2297N repre-\\nsents the Andreev-normal boundary conditions for spin-\\n\\u2191/\\u2193electrons, respectively.\\nOn the other hand, the\\ntemperature-dependent entropy of the MZM-QD subsys-\\ntem (Simp) suggests that the Kondo-like screening pro-.\\n\\nbroken down but the SCE screening preserves. The Lz\\nterm which breaks the SUL(2) symmtry, however, de-\\nstroys the SCE singlet but leaving the A \\u2297N BC un-\\ntouched. Our results are enlightened to both the Kondo\\nand TSC community to dispel the obstacle in theoretical\\npredictions and experimental measurements.\\nII.\\nMODEL AND METHOD\\nThe system we consider is composed of an open topo-\\nlogical superconducting (TSC) wire, a quantum dot, and\\na normal lead as shown in Fig. 1(a). The TSC hosts a\\nlocalized MZM at each boundary, with one side couples\\nto the QD. The Halmitonian is given by H = H0 + H\\u2032.\\nHere H0 is the SUL(2) symmetric Kondo-like impurity\\nmodel of the following form\\nH0 = iJM\\u03b3\\u22121LQD \\u00b7 \\u03be0 + JKLQD \\u00b7 S0 +\\nX\\nk\\n\\u03f5kc\\u2020\\nk\\u03c3ck\\u03c3, (1)\\nwith \\u03b3\\u22121 \\u2261(f + f \\u2020) the MZM operator at the boundary\\nof the TSC, and\\n[\\u03bex\\n0 , \\u03bey\\n0, \\u03bez\\n0] \\u2261\\nh\\ni(c\\u2020\\n0\\u2193\\u2212c0\\u2193), \\u2212(c\\u2020\\n0\\u2193+ c0\\u2193), i(c\\u2020\\n0\\u2191\\u2212c0\\u2191)\\ni\\nform irreducible tensor operators of the SUL(2) group,\\nwhere c0\\u03c3 = P ck\\u03c3 is the local electron annihilation\\noperator.\", \"type\": \"tool\", \"name\": \"document_retriever\", \"id\": \"639f50ac-29c9-4bd3-acdc-e6a1ccbcd6b1\", \"tool_call_id\": \"call_ePaOVcZZKU0K5X97CapsAW6K\", \"status\": \"success\"}}]}, \"tags\": [\"graph:step:6\"], \"metadata\": {\"langgraph_step\": 6, \"langgraph_node\": \"actor\", \"langgraph_triggers\": [\"branch:to:actor\"], \"langgraph_path\": [\"__pregel_pull\", \"actor\"], \"langgraph_checkpoint_ns\": \"actor:eb7aa694-6ecb-6bac-3c9b-d0b38ac8ed9e\"}, \"kwargs\": {\"name\": \"actor\"}}",
        "traceloop.entity.output": "{\"outputs\": {\"messages\": [{\"lc\": 1, \"type\": \"constructor\", \"id\": [\"langchain\", \"schema\", \"messages\", \"AIMessage\"], \"kwargs\": {\"content\": \"\", \"additional_kwargs\": {\"refusal\": null}, \"response_metadata\": {\"token_usage\": {\"completion_tokens\": 61, \"prompt_tokens\": 3314, \"total_tokens\": 3375, \"completion_tokens_details\": {\"accepted_prediction_tokens\": 0, \"audio_tokens\": 0, \"reasoning_tokens\": 0, \"rejected_prediction_tokens\": 0}, \"prompt_tokens_details\": {\"audio_tokens\": 0, \"cached_tokens\": 2176}}, \"model_provider\": \"openai\", \"model_name\": \"gpt-4o-mini-2024-07-18\", \"system_fingerprint\": \"fp_373a14eb6f\", \"id\": \"chatcmpl-DCpi8ECT1LPI541gouz9Yru8QF1B5\", \"service_tier\": \"default\", \"finish_reason\": \"tool_calls\", \"logprobs\": null}, \"type\": \"ai\", \"id\": \"lc_run--019c9083-cdb8-7ed0-9a68-e80acb35743a-0\", \"tool_calls\": [{\"name\": \"document_retriever\", \"args\": {\"s3_uri\": \"s3://agentic-wf/mcp/arxiv_consolidated/download_article-3f4b474fcb286355fc6637db9295740bb01ce3fc.txt\", \"query\": \"core contributions\"}, \"id\": \"call_MY1HkSYKhBllpiIsWCduVHwT\", \"type\": \"tool_call\"}], \"usage_metadata\": {\"input_tokens\": 3314, \"output_tokens\": 61, \"total_tokens\": 3375, \"input_token_details\": {\"audio\": 0, \"cache_read\": 2176}, \"output_token_details\": {\"audio\": 0, \"reasoning\": 0}}, \"invalid_tool_calls\": []}}]}, \"kwargs\": {\"tags\": [\"graph:step:6\"]}}"
